Denver, the capital of Colorado, is an American metropolis dating to the Old West era. Larimer Square, the city’s oldest block, features landmark 19th-century buildings. Museums include the Denver Art Museum, an ultramodern complex known for its collection of indigenous works, and the mansion of famed Titanic survivor Molly Brown. Denver is also a jumping-off point for ski resorts in the nearby Rocky Mountains.

Karaj, the capital of Alborz is the fourth-largest city in the country which hosts a population around 2 millions and also renowned because of its multi-cultural society which represents approxmiately all races, languages, and cultures in Iran so people call it small Iran.
Dinan is a walled Breton town and a commune in the Côtes-d'Armor department in northwestern France. On 1 January 2018, the former commune of Léhon was merged into Dinan.

King City is an unincorporated Canadian community in King, Ontario located north of Toronto. It is the largest community in King Township, with 2,396 dwellings and a population of 6,970 as of the Canada 2016 Census.

Granville is a village in Licking County, Ohio, United States. The population was 5,646 at the 2010 census. The village is located in a rural area of rolling hills in central Ohio. It is 35 miles (56 km) east of Columbus, the state capital, and 7 miles (11 km) west of Newark, the county seat

Kano is the state capital of Kano State in North West, Nigeria. It is situated in the Sahelian geographic region, south of the Sahara. Kano is the commercial nerve centre of Northern Nigeria and is the second largest city in Nigeria

Manchester is a city in North West England, the fifth largest city in the United Kingdom. Manchester has many places for the arts, places for learning, businesses providing media as well as lots of shops. It has two well-known football teams, Manchester United and Manchester City.

Hallstatt is a small town in the district of Gmunden, in the Austrian state of Upper Austria. Situated between the southwestern shore of Hallstätter See and the steep slopes of the Dachstein massif, the town lies in Salzkammergut region, on the national road linking Salzburg and Graz.
Aachen is a small town that shelters the RWTH Aachen, one of the most prestigious university of Germany. Besides, it is located on the border with the Netherlands and Belgium.

Edmonton is the capital city of the province of Alberta, Canada. Sometimes called Canada's Gateway to the North, Edmonton is the farthest north of Canada's large cities and has important road, rail and air transportation links. Edmonton is famous for its rich natural resources, history, culture, and a host of many other attractions.
Bangkok is the capital and most populous city of Thailand. It is known in Thai as Krung Thep Maha Nakhon or simply Krung Thep.
Founded in 1737, San Jose today is a sprawling metropolis. Costa Rica’s capital and the largest city in the country, San Jose is considered to be among the most cosmopolitan cities in Latin America.

The Meteora is a rock formation in central Greece hosting one of the largest and most precipitously built complexes of monasteries. The six (of an original twenty four) monasteries are built on immense natural pillars and hill-like rounded boulders that dominate the local area.
Fortaleza is a capital of the state of Ceará, in northeastern Brazil. The city is known for its beaches, with red cliffs, palm trees, dunes and lagoons

Borken is a small city in the West of Germany with a heritage tracing back into medieval times, with castles and towers being remnants of those days. With it's surrounding municipality it's the home of approximately 42000 residents.
A port city on the east coast of New Zealand, has the biggest sea port in the country and thrives on Kiwifruit exports
Nagpur is a large city in the central Indian state of Maharashtra. The 19th-century Nagpur Central Museum displays items found locally, including fossils, sarcophagi and Mughal weaponry.
The town of Taupō sits at the edge of Australasia's largest lake. Local attractions include trout fishing, mountain biking, skiing, and geothermal parks.
Sacramento is the capital of the State of California and is the fifth largest city in the state. Sacramento has a Mediterranean climate characterized by mild winters and dry summers.

Moab is home to some of the most beatufiful terrain in the United States. Thousands of people from all around the world visit Moab to hike, rock climb, and mountain bike.

Pinetown is a town that is part of the eThekwini Metropolitan Municipality, just inland from Durban in KwaZulu-Natal, South Africa. Pinetown has a population of 144,026 acording to the 2011 census. 55.4% of residence speak isiZulu, 31.4% speak English, 3.8% speak Afrikaans, and 3.3% speak isiXhosa.

San Diego is the eighth-largest city in the United States. It is known for having year-round summer climate with extensive miles of beautiful coastlines. The city has also recently emerged as a center of research for healthcare and biotechnology.

Cincinnati is a major city in the U.S. state of Ohio, and is the government seat of Hamilton County. Settled in 1788, the city is located at the northern side of the confluence of the Licking and Ohio rivers, the latter of which marks the state line with Kentucky. With a city population estimated at 302,605, Cincinnati is the third-largest city in Ohio and 65th in the United States. Cincinnati is also within a day's drive of 49.70% of the United States populace.

Lviv is a city in the west of Ukraine, about 70 kilometers from the border with Poland. The architecture of the city keeps traces of Polish and Austro-Hungarian heritage and combines the styles of Eastern and Central Europe, namely Italy and Germany. In the High Castle park on top of the mountain, the ruins of a 14th-century fortress have been preserved. It offers panoramic views of the green domes of churches and the hills surrounding the city.

Haifa is the third largest city in israel. It is built on the slopes of mount Carmel and is a major port city in israel. It is also known for being home to the Bahai World Center and is an UNESCO World Heritage Site.
Berlin is the capital and largest city of Germany by both area and population. Its 3,748,148 (2018) inhabitants make it the second most populous city proper of the European Union after London.
